Date: Thu, 7 Mar 2024 14:23:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net/x25: fix incorrect parameter validation in the x25_getsockopt() function
Git-commit: d6eb8de2015f0c24822e47356f839167ebde2945
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc1
References: git-fixes

The 'len' variable can't be negative when assigned the result of
'min_t' because all 'min_t' parameters are cast to unsigned int,
and then the minimum one is chosen.

To fix the logic, check 'len' as read from 'optlen',
where the types of relevant variables are (signed) int.

Fixes: 1da177e4c3f4 ("Linux-2.6.12-rc2")
Signed-off-by: Gavrilov Ilia <Ilia.Gavrilov@infotecs.ru>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 net/x25/af_x25.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/x25/af_x25.c b/net/x25/af_x25.c
index f7a7c7798c3b..d18d51412cc0 100644
--- a/net/x25/af_x25.c
+++ b/net/x25/af_x25.c
@@ -460,12 +460,12 @@ static int x25_getsockopt(struct socket *sock, int level, int optname,
 	if (get_user(len, optlen))
 		goto out;
 
-	len = min_t(unsigned int, len, sizeof(int));
-
 	rc = -EINVAL;
 	if (len < 0)
 		goto out;
 
+	len = min_t(unsigned int, len, sizeof(int));
+
 	rc = -EFAULT;
 	if (put_user(len, optlen))
 		goto out;
